definition: to live/to dwell/to stay/to reside/to stop/(suffix indicating firmness, steadiness, or coming to a halt)

sentences.english: This is an empty room, there is nothing in it.
sentences.chinese: 這是一間空屋子，裏面沒人住。

sentences.english: This is an vacant room, nobody live there.
sentences.chinese: 這是一間空屋子，裏面沒人住。

sentences.english: Couldnt live a long time, the room doesn t even have electricity, she was afraid.
sentences.chinese: 房間很久都沒人住，連電都沒有，娜諾很害怕。

sentences.english: This house has not been tenanted for a year.
sentences.chinese: 這房子有一年沒人住了。

sentences.english: This room doesn't seem to be lived in.
sentences.chinese: 這個房間似乎沒人住在裏面。

sentences.english: No one lives in that spidery attic.
sentences.chinese: 沒人住在那個多蜘蛛的閣樓上。
